<materialsCitation box="[2148,2366,829,862]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">
“Caiza,” 
<collectingCountry box="[2266,2362,829,862]" name="Bolivia" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[2063,2657,794,1217]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">
Since its description, status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" box="[2504,2657,869,902]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laephotis">H. laephotis</taxonomicName>
has been confusing. It has been previously considered a full species and later a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi &amp; Landbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[2154,2317,987,1020]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">H. montanus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poeppig" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[2382,2532,987,1020]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotus">H. macrotus</taxonomicName>
. It is now considered a distinct species by most authors based on morphological and ecological evidence. It is frequently mistaken with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Poeppig" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotus">H. macrotus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi &amp; Landbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[2201,2373,1153,1178]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">H. montanus</taxonomicName>
, therefore, accurate data in literature are scarce. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
